      <pb n="1" facs="EHRI-ET-JMP015_01.jpg"/>
      <p rend="center">
        <hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px">Statement</hi>
      </p>
      <p>written with <persName ref="#ehri_et_gibian_hanus">Hanuš <hi rend="letter-spacing: +2px"
            >Gibian</hi></persName>, born <date when="1902-08-15">15. 8. 1902</date> in <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague</placeName>, in the <placeName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2026" type="camp"
          >Nováky</placeName> <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508"
          type="subject">labor camp</term>, <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057999/okres-prievidza.html">Prijevica</placeName> district,
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html"
        >Slovakia</placeName>, residing in <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Prague I.</placeName>, <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3067696/prague.html">Rybná</placeName> 8, <term
          type="subject" ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_czechs">Czech</term> nationality, occupation
        bank clerk.</p>
      <p>From <date when="1941">1941</date> to <date when="1944-09">September 1944</date>, I lived
        with my two-member <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">family</term> (wife and son)
        in the <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-2026" type="camp"
          >Nováky</placeName> <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508"
          type="subject">camp</term>, <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057999/okres-prievidza.html">Prijevica</placeName> district,
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html"
        >Slovakia</placeName>. I <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-556"
          type="subject">worked</term> there in the construction administration. We were <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject">housed</term>
        in wooden buildings; <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819">families</term>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-837" type="subject"
          >lived</term> together, the unmarried separately. The <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-832" type="subject">food</term>
        was fair. At first, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508"
          type="subject">camp</term> was supervised by <orgName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-397">Hlinka’s guards</orgName>,
        who were extremely cruel. Later, <orgName
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-397">Hlinka’s guards</orgName>
        were replaced by <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html"
          >Slovak</placeName>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1125" type="subject"
          >policemen</term>. In <date when="1944-09">September 1944</date>, at the beginning of the
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovak</placeName>
        <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-254"
          >uprising</term>, the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508"
          type="subject">camp</term> was abolished and the <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-483">Jewish inhabitants</term> of
        this <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-508" type="subject"
          >camp</term> were allowed to move freely throughout the space occupied by the <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovak</placeName>
        <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-497">National
          Council</orgName>.</p>
      <p>As a result of the gradual occupation of <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovakia</placeName> by the
          <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-438" type="subject">German
          army</term>, I <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-204">escaped</term> together with
        my <term type="subject" ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819"
          >family</term> to the area around <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3061186/banska-bystrica.html">Banská Bystrica</placeName>,
        where I worked in the state refinery in <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060335/dubove.html">Dubová</placeName> until <date
          when="1944-10-28">October 28th 1944</date>. When the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-438" type="subject">German
          army</term> approached <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3061186/banska-bystrica.html">Banská Bystrica</placeName>, we
        were forced to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262"
          type="subject">hide</term> in the <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3057568/slovak-republic.html">Slovak</placeName> mountains.
        After wandering aimlessly for three whole days, during which the <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Germans</term> twice shot at us, we were captured on
          <date when="1944-11-01">1. 11. 1944</date>. <term type="subject"
          ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">German</term>
        <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject"
          >SSmen</term> gathered all of us together in a meadow and asked us if we were Jews. Those
        who could provide papers proving they were <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-373">Aryan</term> were released.
        The Jews were told to immediately hand over their watches, money, and all of the valuables
        that they had on them. The <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SSmen</term>
        told us that we would no longer need them. Then, the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SS</term>
        leader ordered us to be transported and notified us that a patrol of 2 <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1097" type="subject"
          >soldiers</term> would accompany us, promising that nothing would happen to us. On our way
        down from the mountains, we were joined by 4 more <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SSmen</term>,
        so there was a total of 6. They took us to a meadow where the <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1216" type="subject">SSmen</term>
        hung back and ordered us to walk toward <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3061186/banska-bystrica.html">Banská Bystrica</placeName> and
        to stay together. After we had gone forward for about 10 steps, they began to shoot us in
        the back. They fired until everyone (42 people) lay <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term> or
        half-dead. They then examined each body and took whatever they liked, and <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
          >murdered</term> anyone who wasn’t <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term>
        yet with a shot to the dead. I pretended to be <term
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term> as
        well as a 14-year-old <term type="subject"
          ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824">girl</term> who was covered
        by her father’s overcoat. By a miracle, she was saved. This happened on <date
          when="1944-11-01">November 1st, 1944</date>, at 13:00 in the gap between <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3059328/kozi-chrbat.html">Kozí Chrbát</placeName> and
          <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3058043/prasiva.html">Prašiva</placeName> in
          the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3058517/nizke-tatry.html">Lower Tatra
          Mountains</placeName>, near the village of <placeName
          ref="http://www.geonames.org/3060117/hiadel.html">Hiadel</placeName>.</p>

